Optiv (Cybersecurity Company) - Wikipedia






















 






Optiv (Cybersecurity Company)

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search






This article contains content that is written like an advertisement. Please help improve it by removing promotional content and inappropriate external links, and by adding encyclopedic content written from a neutral point of view. (March 2017) (Learn how and when to remove this template message)







This article is an orphan, as no other articles link to it. Please introduce links to this page from related articles; try the Find link tool for suggestions. (December 2012)



Optiv Security





Type

Private


Industry
Information security


Predecessor
Accuvant and FishNet Security


Founded
2015 (formed from the merger of Accuvant and FishNet Security)


Headquarters
Denver, Colorado, United States



Area served

Worldwide



Key people




Dan Burns (CEO)
David Roshak (CFO)
Paul Lehman (Chief Information Officer)





Services
Cyber Security Services


Revenue



US$2 billion (2015)
US$1.5 billion (2014)






Number of employees

1,500 (2016)


Website
Optiv.com


Optiv Security ("Optiv") is a privately owned information security company based in Denver, Colorado, United States. Optiv is a comprehensive pure-play cyber security solutions provider in North America.
Optiv helps businesses, governments and educational institutions plan, build and run successful security programs through the right combination of products, services and solutions related to security program strategy, enterprise risk and compliance, threat and vulnerability management, enterprise incident management, security architecture and implementation, training, identity and access management, managed security, and third-party risk management.
Optiv has served more than 7,500 clients in more than 70 countries over the past three years. These clients are various sizes across multiple industries, including Fortune 500 companies. Optiv maintains partnerships with more than 350 of the leading security product manufacturers.



Contents


1 History
2 Recognition

2.1 2016
2.2 2015


3 References
4 External links



History[edit]
On November 5, 2014, security firms Accuvant and FishNet Security announced that they would join forces to create a new, yet to be named company.[1] The merger would create a roughly $1.5 billion information security giant with solutions covering nearly every aspect of cyberdefense.[2]
The merger was completed on February 2, 2015 when the company announced that the previously announced transaction had closed.[3] The new company was owned primarily by the Blackstone Group, a private equity firm that acquired a majority stake of Accuvant in March 2014.[4]
On April 21, 2015, Accuvant and FishNet Security announced plans to launch their new, combined corporate name and brand, and to begin conducting business as Optiv Security in summer 2015.[5]
During the Black Hat USA 2015 conference, on August 5, 2015 Accuvant and FishNet Security announced that it had completed its transformation merger and was now conducting business as Optiv Security.[6] It also launched its new brand at the conference.
On February 1, 2017, Optiv announced that it was acquired by the global investment firm KKR.[7]
Recognition[edit]
2016[edit]

October 2016: Two Palo Alto Networks NextWave 2016 awards: Professional Services Partner of the Year for the Americas and Excellence in Support for the Americas[8]
September 2016: Named Colorado’s top company in the technology, software and communications industry by ColoradoBiz magazine[9]
September 2016: Named to Inc. 5000, a ranking of the nation’s fastest-growing private companies in North America[10]
August 2016: Ranked on The Channel Company's 2016 CRN Fast Growth 150
June 2016: Ranked number 25 on The Channel Company's 2016 CRN Solution Provider 500[11]
January 2016: 2015 Bit9 + Carbon Black Best National Partner Award[12]

2015[edit]

October 2015: Ranked on The Channel Company's 2015 CRN Fast Growth 150 list[13]
August 2015: Palo Alto Networks 2015 Americas Partner of the Year[14]

