This job listing has expired and the position may no longer be open for hire.






    Solution Marketing Manager - Partners and Products
      at Optiv Security Inc.
  

    Posted in Sales over 1 year ago.
  

      This job brought to you by eQuest


Type: Full-Time
Location: Denver, Colorado
  
Job Description:

Optiv is the largest holistic pure-play cyber security solutions provider in North America. The company’s diverse and talented employees are committed to helping businesses, governments and educational institutions plan, build and run successful security programs through the right combination of products, services and solutions related to security program strategy, enterprise risk and consulting, threat and vulnerability management, enterprise incident management, security architecture and implementation, training, identity and access management, and managed security.Created in 2015 as a result of the Accuvant and FishNet Security merger, Optiv is a Blackstone (NYSE:BX) portfolio company that has served more than 12,000 clients of various sizes across multiple industries, offers an extensive geographic footprint, and has premium partnerships with more than 300 of the leading security product manufacturers. For more information, please visit www.optiv.com.Solution Marketing Manager - Partners and ProductsOptiv’s Solutions Management department is seeking an energetic, self-driven Solutions Manager to be part of a team that owns the definition and positioning of the information security services, solutions, and products that Optiv offers to clients.  The role will involve a high degree of accountability, coordination of programs and projects and development of marketing solutions and tools collaborating with multiple departments.  To achieve these goals, the role will require a practical knowledge of marketing and the information security landscape.  Primary ResponsibilitiesThe Solutions Manager will work with various departments within Optivwell as external partners, to define and position the information security services and solutions that Optiv offers to clients.  Activities include:Own the go-to-market planning and positioning of services and solutions in a domain of offerings (products and services) with a goal to drive increased awareness and salesDefinition and creation of marketing and sales content, such as briefs, battle cards, data sheets, presentations, and sales scripts that increase awareness and engagement of solutions that position and differentiate offerings in the marketUnderstanding the information security landscape and the domain of offerings that are currently offered, what should be offered, the features provided, advantages to the client, and benefits that are addressed.Analysis of the information security market, ability to address client problems, competitive analysis, and identifying new solutions to add to the portfolio of offeringsSales enablement – communicate the value proposition of the products to the sales team and develop the sales tools that support the selling process of your productsCoordinate the launch of new services and align activities with multiple departmentsCollaborate with the corporate brand and public relations departments for promotion of solutionsCollaborate with the marketing programs department on events and campaignsCollaborate with the lead development department on identifying and nurturing marketing qualified leadsDefine content for sales training and new updated offeringsREQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS:+8 years experience in any combination of: sales, marketing, business development, partner management, channel sales and managementDemonstrated ownership of marketing content, campaigns, and solutionsIndustry experience in Information Security or leading-edge IT solutionsSuccessful participation in projects and programs that drive additional revenue and lower cost of sales and marketingUnderstanding of sales forecasts and marketing cost managementExperience working in a distributed work environmentInnovative approaches to marketing, positioning, and sales enablementStrong interpersonal skills for collaboration and achieving team goalsExcellent written and oral communication in marketing copy and technical writingDESIRED QUALIFICATIONS:Experience in product marketing and/or product management in IT, networking or securityExperience in the channel resale and distribution businessBusiness development and partner managementBachelor’s degree in Marketing or technical field and/or MBAMUST HAVE:Valid Driver’s LicenseAbility to work greater than 40 hours per week as neededAbility to travel up to 15% percent of the time*LI-JW1Optiv is an Equal Opportunity Employer.  We are committed to a work environment where everyone is treated with respect. It is our policy to recruit, employ, retain, promote, terminate and otherwise treat any and all employees and job applicants on the basis of merit, qualifications and competence. We will provide equal employment opportunities without regard to race, color, age, sex, religion, national origin, disability, military or veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, marital status, genetic information, or any other legally protected status or characteristic.We will also take affirmative action as called for by applicable laws and executive orders to ensure that minority group individuals, females, disabled veterans, recently separated veterans, other protected veterans, Armed Forces Service Medal veterans, and qualified disabled persons are introduced into our workforce and considered for promotional opportunities.This policy prohibits retaliation or adverse employment action against anyone who exercises his or her rights under this policy or any anti-discrimination law, who cooperates in any company investigation, or who participates in any investigation or proceeding by any governmental agency.
 

 

